This record pins the TYPED-WRITE shape: what generated create/update code
produces when it serializes entity values through the emitter (note the
date is unquoted — a String value that happens to look like a date emits
as a bare scalar; it round-trips as a string regardless). The sibling
`ship-the-emitter` golden pins the HAND-AUTHORED parse shape instead;
the two roles are deliberately separate files.
